                            <comment id="15415116" author="githubbot" created="Wed, 10 Aug 2016 11:00:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;GitHub user 1ambda opened a pull request:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/1717&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/1717&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-3742&quot; title=&quot;Can&amp;#39;t run connect-distributed.sh with -daemon flag&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-3742&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-3742&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Can&apos;t run bin/connect-*.sh with -daemon flag&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;ol&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Problem&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ol&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;    Current connect scripts (`connect-distributed.sh`, `connect-standalone.sh`) do not support `-daemon` flag even if users specify the flag&lt;br/&gt;
    since `kafka-run-class.sh` requires that the`-daemon` flag should precede other arguments (e.g. class name)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;ol&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Solution&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ol&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;    Do the same thing like `kafka-server-start.sh`&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Parse a command&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Add `-daemon` to `$EXTRA_ARGS` if exists&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;



